# Project 1: Real-Time Financial Transaction Pipeline

## What This Project Is

An end-to-end data pipeline that ingests streaming financial transaction data through Apache Kafka, processes batches using PySpark DataFrames and RDDs on Hadoop HDFS, and loads clean data into a PostgreSQL data warehouse. It handles 500K+ simulated records with real-time batch ingestion, has automated validation so that bad records get flagged before reaching the warehouse, and includes SQL analytics with JOINs and window functions to generate daily settlement reports and catch transaction anomalies.

**GitHub Repo Name:** `financial-data-pipeline`
**Owner:** `Ch-Suharsha`
**Tech Stack:** Python, Apache Kafka, PySpark, Hadoop (HDFS), PostgreSQL, Docker

---

